-- GM, Peugeot to Decide on Brazil Factory This Month, Veja Says
-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 2012-05-19T14:19:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-19/gm-peugeot-to-decide-on-brazil-factory-this-month-veja-says.html
General Motors Co. (GM)  and PSA Peugeot
Citroen will decide on a 1-billion-euro ($1.28 billion)
investment to build a factory in  Brazil  by the end of this
month, Veja magazine reported in its Radar column, without
saying where it got the information.  The plant may be built in Rio de Janeiro or Minas Gerais
state, the Sao Paulo-based magazine said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in Sao Paulo at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  